30/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The 15 December deadline for the campaign of voluntary surrender of illegally held weapons in Macedonia will not be extended, the campaign's co-ordinate body operation officer, Blagoja Markovski, said on Saturday (29 November). 
Markovski announced the end of the second phase of the operation, and said the third and final phase would start on 5 December. 
He added that the collection of 5,000-6,000 weapons should be considered a success for the initiative. 
(MIA, Makfax - 29/11/03)
